All Classes and Interfaces

Class
Description
AlgaArm
Controls the alga arm mechanism for game piece manipulation.
Climb
Controls the robot's climbing mechanism for end-game scoring.
Constants
Constants used throughout the robot code.
Constants.AlgaArmConstants
Constants for the alga arm mechanism.
Constants.ClimbConstants
Constants for the climbing mechanism.
Constants.CoralConstants
Constants for the coral mechanism (elevator, arm, and intake).
Constants.OIConstants
Constants for operator interface (OI).
Constants.PID
PID control constants container.
Constants.RobotConstants
Constants for basic robot characteristics.
CoralHandler
Controls the Coral mechanism, a multi-joint manipulator consisting of an elevator, arm, and intake.
DropAlgaCommand
Command that runs the alga intake in reverse until the game piece is released.
DropCoralCommand
Command that runs the coral intake in reverse until the game piece is released.
IntakeAlgaCommand
Command that runs the alga intake until either a game piece is detected or the command is cancelled.
IntakeCoralCommand
Command that runs the coral intake until either a game piece is detected or the command is cancelled.
LimitedPIDSubsystem
Represents a PID-controlled subsystem with limit switches and position control.
LimitedPIDSubsystem.ControlMode
Control mode for the subsystem.
LimitedPIDSubsystem.SubsystemState
State of position knowledge for a subsystem.
LimitSwitch
Abstraction for limit switches with different backend implementations.
LimitSwitch.LimitSwitchConfig
Configuration class to simplify limit switch creation.
LimitSwitch.LimitSwitchType
Enum representing the type of limit switch backend.
LimitSwitchPair
Manages a pair of limit switches for a mechanism's min and max positions.
Main
Robot initialization class that starts the robot code execution.
Robot
Main robot class that manages the robot's lifecycle and operational modes.
RobotContainer
Main robot configuration class that binds controls and commands to subsystems.
Swerve
Manages the robot's swerve drive system, providing control over movement, autonomous path following, and odometry tracking.
